-color has-very-light-gray-background-color\">What is WordPress? At its core,&nbsp;<strong>WordPress is the simplest, most popular way to create your own website or blog.&nbsp;</strong>In fact, WordPress powers&nbsp;over 35.2%&nbsp;of all the websites on the Internet. Yes – more than one in four websites that you visit are likely powered by WordPress.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></section>\n<!-- /wp:uagb/section -->\n\n<!-- wp:uagb/section {\"classMigrate\":true,\"block_id\":\"a3bb154a-2631-4618-b684-4fbace2f1df7\",\"contentWidth\":\"full_width\"} -->\n<section class=\"wp-block-uagb-section uagb-section__wrap uagb-section__background-undefined uagb-block-a3bb154a-2631-4618-b684-4fbace2f1df7\"><div class=\"uagb-section__overlay\"></div><div class=\"uagb-section__inner-wrap\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\",\"backgroundColor\":\"very-light-gray\",\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background has-text-align-center has-medium-font-size has-very-light-gray-background-color\"> On a slightly more technical level, WordPress is an open-source content management system licensed under GPLv2, which means that anyone can use or modify the WordPress software for free. A content management system is basically a tool that makes it easy to manage important aspects of your website – like content – without needing to know anything about programming. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></section>\n<!-- /wp:uagb/section -->\n\n<!-- wp:uagb/section {\"classMigrate\":true,\"block_id\":\"731314c3-7c35-47d3-9016-0e50dfba9f6f\",\"contentWidth\":\"full_width\",\"backgroundType\":\"none\"} -->\n<section class=\"wp-block-uagb-section uagb-section__wrap uagb-section__background-none uagb-block-731314c3-7c35-47d3-9016-0e50dfba9f6f\"><div class=\"uagb-section__overlay\"></div><div class=\"uagb-section__inner-wrap\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\",\"backgroundColor\":\"very-light-gray\",\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background has-text-align-center ha